Oct 16 2009	CELL PHONE STOLEN BY EMPLOYEE - DON'T STAY HERE	I am really disappointed that my cell phone was stolen by one of the employees. I had left the phone in the room and called 15 minutes later. When I came back to pick it up, it was not only missing, but had been turned off (which to me was further proof of it haven been stolen). I found the staff that day to be unfriendly, unhelpful and uncaring. The worst part was the way it was handled by the manager/owner. When I finally got ahold of her 3 days after the incident, she spoke very harshly with no concern for what had happened and told me that I was harrassing the employees, never asking me one question. I couldn't get a word in edgewise and was never even able to tell her what happened. She just assumed that her employees were telling the truth. The room was fine and I would have stayed there regularly on our visits to UCSF Medical Center, but after this incident I just won't do it. I will not support someone who runs their business in that manner. I hope you consider doing the same.	
Aug 16 2009 	Would stay here again	We stayed here because of the price and decent reviews. It was a decent hotel. It was clean enough which is most important to me when traveling. The hotel is nicely located to public transportation, so once you park, stay parked. There is limited parking space available. The hotel staff were friendly, but not overly friendly. We basically slept here. We didn't hang out during the day and there aren't any fun amenities to warrant being there during the day. Stay here if you are on a budget and looking for a clean room. The free breakfast is juice, muffins and pastries. It's not substantial or appealing.	
Feb 26 2009 	Tired and worn out	I have been staying at this place off and on for the last twenty years, at the times when I wanted to save some money. So I don't expect things to be like they are at the Mark Hopkins, Fairmont, or other SF places I prefer. But our recent stay has led me to re-evaluate the &quot;bargain&quot; of staying at the Days Inn at Civic Center. For one thing, there seems to have been little or no serious or even cosmetic upgrades here for about ten years. The bed was rather soft. Housekeeping kept the bathrooms clean, but the bathmat should have been replaced long ago. No vacuum ever touched the corners of the room during the four nights I stayed there, and for those four days and nights the large mirror by the desk retained the big and greasy fingerprint smears which had greeted me when I checked in. Most of the desk staff was pleasant but close to incompetent. My business partner (in the room next door) and I both had repeated problems with our keys not working, which caused us to make repeated trips to the office for new ones. The night clerk did not even make a pretense of being polite or friendly.I would no longer recommend this place to anyone except to those for whom saving a few bucks is more important than anything else including your self-respect.	
Aug 31 2008 	Central Location 	Summary: Nothing fancy, but a great value, especially if arriving by car.Pros: Helpful front desk; large, clean rooms (ours had fridge &amp; microwave-- but no supplies); central location on bus line; good restaurants nearby; free continental breakfast, wi-fi, and on-site parking.Cons:1) It's best to grab a parking spot when you get there, then walk/commute during your stay. The motel lot is small, and there was shattered safety glass on most nearby streets.... 2) If you don't like stairs, be prepared to wait. One very small, tired, elevator serves 4 floors and about 40 rooms.	
Jan 31 2008 	Not bad for the price	My fiance and I stayed here when we saw The Nutcracker last December. It has a good, central location in downtown SF, in walking distance of good restaurants, the Opera House, and some shopping. The room was comfy and clean and we had a good night's rest.A couple of things: The continental breakfast leaves much to be desired. I was hoping for some freshly cooked food, or at least something semi-healthy, but all they had was a basket of junk food and some coffee. I know it's free, but come on! The other thing is that we never received our 9:00 am wake-up call. We just happened to wake up at around 9:30. When we brought it up to the clerk at check out, he just mumbled something about how the computer takes care of wake-up calls. Other than that, no major complaints!	
Jan 6 2008 	Better Than Expected!	After some of the reviews I read about this place, I was dreading staying here! However, I was almost completely happy!The location is ok, a bit out of the busy area &amp; if you walk to &amp; from the hotel, you do walk through quite a rough place. It's more than ok during the day, however at night was always made sure we got a cab back.I was happy with the hotel itself. A nice spacious room with 2 comfortable double beds, both clean. A good sized tv with HBO etc. A small attempt at a kitchen ie, sink, fridge &amp; microwave, all were clean. My only issue was the bathroom. The shower, toilet &amp; sink area we fine, clean &amp; in full working order. What was my issue I hear you say!? Well, don't be alarmed but there were ants! Not loads of them but probably 2 or 3 on the bathroom walls. I would not allow this to put you off but I would like to think my review was honest!Other than that, the receptionist was very helpful, gave us directions etc &amp; stored our suitcases on the day we were leaving.For the price, you cannot complain!	
