Oct 11 2005 	Nice for the Price	Clean, comfortable and close to a decent set of restaurants. For the money it was a nice place to stay. I walked the 1 1/2 miles to the Moscone center every day and although not always scenic - the walk seemed safe. For a bare bones place it had more than I expected.The wireless was out most of the week - that was a disappointment.	
Jun 13 2005	A Really Nice Surprise	My husband and I spent three nights at this Days Inn. Perhaps it was the state of the Days Inn that we had stayed in the night before checking in here, but we were surprised and pleased at the rooms at this location. Our room was VERY clean and looked like they had updated the decor a bit to attempt to give it a &quot;charming&quot; look. The result was that while not high quality decor, it was very nice. The room was comfortable and clean. The bathrooms are HUGE. We peeked in at a jacuzzi room, considering getting one, but the bathrooms are basically the same size and the jacuzzi room just has a bigger bathtub with jets. Really not worth the extra $20, unless you really want to jacuzzi solo.We were on the third floor, but there is a small lift (I say lift rather than elevator, because... it's a lift... and small) so you can get your luggage up easily. You can hear some street noise, or I should say walkway noise, but that's not uncommon in a motel and it wasn't too bad. But we were there at a pretty low capacity time, too.There is limited free parking which is wonderful, but they do only have about 25 spaces. If you were there at a busy time, you might run into a challenge getting a parking spot if you returned late, but while we were there we had no problems and there was plenty of parking. That was a huge relief! It is in walking distance to a few of the sites, mainly to the civic center area, but we had a vehicle, so we drove most everywhere we went leaving me with few recommendations of places to walk to.The staff was very friendly - both the desk folks and the cleaning people were great. As far as the breakfast provided, that inlcuded coffee, juices, and tea and individually wrapped pastries and Otis Spunkmeyer muffins. I think there was some fruit there, too. It wasn't a lot, but it was a nice light breakfast to get started with or a snack until we could eat breakfast. It was also nice to be able to grab a couple extra of the little muffins to take along for snacks while sightseeing. I have very low expectations of complimentary motel breakfasts, so to me it was just fine. If you want a hot breakfast with eggs and french toast, you might want to try a restaurant.All in all, we enjoyed our stay at the Civic Cneter Days Inn and will likely use this property again on future visits to San Francisco when we are trying to save a little cash for doing the fun stuff. I recommend this location and if you go in expecting a Days Inn, you'll be pleased at what you get.	
