Apr 3 2004	decent place	I stayed here and had a good experience, especially considering the killer rate I got! The rooms were recently refurbished, and the staff was quite proud of this. They called me after I'd been in my room for twenty minutes to ask if everything was satisfactory. Nice. The room was clean and tastefully done, but small and standard for a hotel chain. The rooms all face a parking lot but I wasn't bothered by noise. I liked the location, there were many restaurants in Hayes Valley around the corner to choose from. Also walking distance to the Muni trains and BART for getting to and from the airport. I would stay here again, especially if I received the amazingly low price I got during my last visit. Sure beats the Travelodge on Market St. that I stayed at a year ago.	
